## 3. Review Gates (Approval Protocol)

No code merges without passing ALL applicable gates:

### Gate 1: Novice Readability (Agent N1)
- [ ] Every function has a JSDoc comment explaining what it does, its parameters, and return value
- [ ] Complex logic has inline comments explaining WHY (not what)
- [ ] Magic numbers are named constants with explanatory comments
- [ ] Variable names are self-documenting (no single-letter names except loop counters)
- [ ] New files include a header block: purpose, who it's for, how it connects to the rest of the project

### Gate 2: Semantic Layer Compliance (Agents D1 + PBI1)
- [ ] Every data point rendered in the UI has a `MetricKey` in `powerbi/metric-registry.json`
- [ ] Every JSON key used in charts/tables/forms is documented in `docs/DATA-DICTIONARY.md`
- [ ] New data fields include: `metricKey`, `unit`, `goldColumns` mapping, `authoritativeSourceUrls`
- [ ] Placeholder values (e.g., `{hospital_savings}`) are tracked in `powerbi/semantic-layer-registry.json`
- [ ] Story submission forms produce structured JSON with fields that map to `fact_story_submission.*`

### Gate 3: PA 340B Compliance (Agents C1 + A1)
- [ ] All statistics match `state-data.js`, HAP fact sheets, and cited authoritative sources
- [ ] No invented data — if unsure, flag for human review
- [ ] 340B, contract pharmacy, PBM, HRSA terminology used correctly
- [ ] "Why it matters" line accompanies every stat and advocacy bullet
- [ ] HAP position language is accurate and current

### Gate 4: Security (Agent S1)
- [ ] No `innerHTML`, `outerHTML`, or `eval()` with user/dynamic input
- [ ] Hash state validated against allowlist
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or credentials
- [ ] 340b-BASIC.html: local scripts only, no CDN, no localStorage
- [ ] Share/print flows do not leak internal state

### Gate 5: Performance (Agent P1)
- [ ] No layout thrashing (batch DOM reads/writes)
- [ ] Scroll handlers are passive + rAF
- [ ] Animations use `transform`/`opacity` only; respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- [ ] No heavy always-on observers without justification

### Gate 6: Cross-Surface Consistency (Agent PM1)
- [ ] Changes to `340b.css`, `hap-design-tokens.css`, `hap-nav-shared.js` checked against ALL surfaces
- [ ] Print pipeline (`print.html`, `print-view.css`) verified after DOM changes
- [ ] OW report not broken by shared style changes
- [ ] BASIC version constraints preserved

### Gate 7: Power BI / Warehouse Readiness (Agent PBI1)
- [ ] All dynamic placeholders cataloged with their future warehouse source
- [ ] `DataLayer` methods return Promise-wrapped data matching Gold schema shapes
- [ ] Chart configs in `config/chart-configs.js` use `MetricKey` identifiers
- [ ] Forms produce JSON whose keys match `fact_*` table columns
- [ ] `powerbi/metric-registry.json` updated for any new metrics

