## 4. Semantic Layer Tracking

### 4a. Dynamic Placeholder Registry

Every placeholder in the codebase that will eventually pull from a warehouse or Power BI must be tracked. The canonical registry is `powerbi/semantic-layer-registry.json`.

**Required fields per placeholder:**

```json
{
  "placeholderId": "hospital_savings",
  "displayContext": "KPI card on Home tab",
  "currentSource": "hard-coded in 340b-mobile.html data-count attribute",
  "staticValue": "7.95",
  "metricKey": "COMMUNITY_BENEFIT_TOTAL_BILLIONS",
  "goldTable": "fact_dashboard_kpi",
  "goldColumn": "ValueNumeric",
  "unit": "USD_BILLIONS",
  "updateFrequency": "Annual",
  "owner": "HAP Advocacy + 340B Health",
  "dataLayerMethod": "DataLayer.getKPIs()",
  "pbiReady": true
}
```

### 4b. Chart & Table Semantic Mapping

Every chart, table, or visualization must declare:

| Property | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `chartId` | Unique identifier (e.g., `protection-map`, `audit-comparison`) |
| `dataSource` | Which `DataLayer` method feeds it |
| `fields` | Array of field names with their `MetricKey` mappings |
| `pbiVisualType` | Suggested Power BI visual (Map, Card, Bar, Table) |
| `goldTables` | Which Gold tables the chart will query |

### 4c. Story Form Semantic Contract

The story submission form (`DataLayer.submitStory()`) must produce JSON matching:

```json
{
  "hospitalName": "string → fact_story_submission.HospitalName",
  "county": "string → fact_story_submission.County",
  "category": "enum(Patient Access|Community Benefit|Rural Care|Financial Impact) → fact_story_submission.Category",
  "storyText": "string(500) → fact_story_submission.StoryText",
  "contactEmail": "string|null → fact_story_submission.ContactEmail",
  "submittedAt": "ISO8601 → fact_story_submission.SubmittedAt"
}
```

