## 11. Summary-first review protocol (token-efficient)

When acting as **Supervisor** on agent output (code, data, charts, maps, forms, PDFs), **minimize context** without sacrificing auditability. Expand to full file reads only when a gate fails or a warning needs proof.

### 11a. Modular review (run mentally in this order)

| Module | What to verify first (summary / metadata) | Escalate to full code when |
|--------|-------------------------------------------|-----------------------------|
| **Data integrity** | Which fields changed; claimed source (HAP, HRSA, `state-data.js`, metric-registry); no new numbers without citation | New KPI, copy stat, or JSON field without registry/dictionary |
| **Semantic layer** | New `MetricKey`? Registry + `semantic-layer-registry.json` + `DATA-DICTIONARY` delta | Chart/form keys undocumented or mismatched to Gold |
| **Compliance / advocacy** | Terminology (340B, contract pharmacy, PBM); stats match approved sources; no invented policy | Advocacy copy change or HRSA/340B claim |
| **Code quality / novice** | File list, function names, “touched surfaces”; JSDoc on new exports | Obscure logic, security path, or FAIL on readability |
| **Integration / QA** | Blast radius (BASIC, print, OW); tests run (`dashboard-audit.py`) | Cross-cutting CSS/nav or print pipeline |

### 11b. Preferred input from sub-agents

Ask other agents (or humans) to lead with a **short block** before pasting large diffs:

```
Scope: [files or feature]
Data: [source doc / state-data key / MetricKey]
Surfaces: [340b-mobile | 340b | BASIC | print | …]
Risk: [low | medium | high]
```

Review that block first; request **unified diffs or specific line ranges** only if ⚠ or ❌.

### 11c. Structured supervisor output (concise)

Use this format by default; **add detail only under ⚠ and ❌**:

```
✔ [module]: [one line]
⚠ [module]: [one line] → action: …
❌ [module]: [one line] → must fix: …
VERDICT: APPROVED | NEEDS REVISION | REJECTED
Sources: [e.g. state-data.js CONFIG; HRSA FY24 audits; HAP Mar 2026 PDFs]
```

### 11d. Novice-friendliness (efficient)

- Require **file-level purpose** and **JSDoc on public functions** for new/changed modules; avoid essay-length inline comments.
- Flag **unclear names** and **missing high-level section comments** in ⚠; reserve line-by-line feedback for ❌.

### 11e. Continuous improvement (supervisor self-check)

After a review batch, ask briefly: *Did any module get skipped? Did I approve without a source for a number?* Update mental checklist when new surfaces appear (e.g. new AI helper, new hospital layer, new PDF block). When using the **Node wave agents**, approvals and evidence belong in `data/archive/` per `docs/MULTI_AGENT_SYSTEM.md`; Cursor-only reviews stay in chat/PR until a human logs them.

### 11f. Data verification (summary-first)

- **Canonical static data:** `state-data.js`, `CONFIG`, `docs/DATA-DICTIONARY.md`, `powerbi/metric-registry.json` — numbers must match; **do not invent** ranges or “HAP 2024” figures unless that vintage is what the repo actually cites.
- **Common authoritative buckets** (use only what the change claims): HAP dated fact sheets / talking points (e.g. March 2026 materials in repo), **HRSA** Program Integrity / OPA, **Commonwealth Fund** where the dashboard explicitly cites (e.g. market-share context), **MultiState / ASHP / Essential Hospitals** for state law, **DHS / Medicaid duplicate-discount** context only when copy or data explicitly references it.
- **Methodology:** Feedback must name **file + field or MetricKey**, not vague “per report.” Escalate to full diff if summaries disagree with `state-data.js`.

### 11g. Workflow-specific checks (maps → AI helpers)

Use **metadata first**; full code only if ⚠/❌.

| Workflow | Summary to request from agent | Supervisor spot-check |
|----------|------------------------------|------------------------|
| **Maps** | Data file(s); lat/lng source; fields on markers/popups; failure isolation (print/share OK?) | No raw user input in DOM; state codes allowlisted; hospital points documented in `DATA-DICTIONARY` / `semantic-layer-registry` if new |
| **Charts** | Chart id; fields + `MetricKey`; title/axis labels; novice clarity | Keys in `metric-registry` / `chart-configs`; DAX/table name target if new |
| **Story form** | Payload shape; max lengths; storage target | Matches `fact_story_submission.*`; `DataLayer.submitStory`; no `innerHTML` with user text |
| **PDF / print** | What snapshot DOM changed; source strip still correct | `print.html` / `print-view.css`; no stale stats vs `state-data.js`; map visibility rules preserved |
| **AI helpers** | Function; input/output shape; offline-safe? | `modules/ai-helpers.js` modular; structured return types documented; no secrets / no fabricated stats in narratives |

### 11h. Compliance & advocacy (PA 340B)

- **Program concepts:** contract pharmacy, covered entity, duplicate discount / Medicaid (only as accurately stated in approved copy), **HRSA** oversight — terminology must match HAP-approved usage; flag overclaims or missing “why it matters” where the product standard requires it.
- **Policy citations:** If an agent adds statute/reg references, verify against project-approved sources or flag for **human** SME review; supervisor does not invent legal citations.

### 11i. Output expectation (Opus / Cursor)

For every agent deliverable, default to **§11c** format (`✔` / `⚠` / `❌`, `VERDICT`, `Sources`). Request **full code or datasets** only for flagged items. Preserve **novice-friendly** module headers + JSDoc on public APIs without verbose inline narration.

