## 12. Meta-Supervisor (second-pass audit)

The **Meta-Supervisor** is a deliberate **second lens** on the same change, after the primary Supervisor (§1–§11) signs off or requests revision. It does **not** replace security rules, `SECURE-FORCE.md`, or human release gates.

### 12a. Role

| Layer | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| **Supervisor** | Gates: data, semantic layer, compliance, novice readability, cross-surface, token-efficient review (§11). |
| **Meta-Supervisor** | Audits **whether the Supervisor missed anything**: blind spots (BASIC, print, OW), unstated blast radius, silent data drift, missing registry updates, “approved” copy that still invents numbers, semantic key hygiene (valid JSON identifiers). |

### 12b. When to run (lightweight)

- After **large** or **cross-cutting** merges (shared CSS, `state-data.js`, `DataLayer`, print pipeline).
- When introducing **new modules**, **new metrics**, or **API-shaped** payloads.
- Optionally on a **human-triggered** “meta review” request — default remains **summary-first** (§11).

### 12c. Meta-Supervisor output (concise)

```
META-REVIEW: [PASS | NEEDS FOLLOW-UP]
Blind spots checked: [BASIC | print | OW | mobile | PBI registry | …]
Findings: [none | bullet list]
Digest row: [see §13a or §13b]
```

